wool-blind
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adjective
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[of sheep, particularly Romneys and Merinos]  unable to see, due to wool growing over the eyes.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka wool blind
Citations
Date: 14/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Eye-clip.</i> To cut the wool away from round a sheep's eyes. If this is not done, the wool, especially on merinos is apt to grow over the eyes and make the sheep <i>wool-blind. </i>
Notes:

